# SYNTHESIS_V2 : CSSLv3 REFRAMED — NO DEFERRAL, NO TIME-CAP
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# § I> prior synthesis (research/99_SYNTHESIS.csl) assumed community-credibility
#      ≡ solo-PhD-per-feature ≡ year-scale phasing
# § I> actual-context : Apocky + Claude-pair + 2-day-work-bursts
# § I> ∀ "deferred v2" = cope • reframe pulls-everything-forward

§ THESIS-V2  ← §§ S2.1
  CSSLv3 ≡ consent=OS encoded-in-typesystem-structure
         ⊕ engine-primitives-as-lang-primitives
         ⊕ hardware-first (Arc A770 Xe-HPG + AVX2/AVX-512)
         ⊕ full-IFC + full-effects + full-AD + full-linear + full-refinement
         ⊕ single-source dual-emit (CPU × GPU × console × mobile × web)
         ⊕ orthogonal-persistence (Pharo-class live-dev-loop)
         ⊕ Futamura-P3 self-applicable-partial-eval
         ⊕ density=sovereignty (CSLv3-as-native-surface option)
         ⊕ Level-Zero direct-to-metal compute + instrumentation-first
  I> NOT "better Slang" NOT "better Jai" • CSSLv3 = Apocky-framework-as-lang

§ THE-18-REFRAMES AS INTEGRATED-DESIGN-MOVES  ← §§ S2.2
  ¬ list-of-features-to-add
  ≡ single coherent-design where-each-move implies-others

  R1 : IFC-typesystem (Jif DLM) ←→ effect-system {Sensitive<dom>}
    ⇒ consent=OS structurally-enforced ¬ policy-enforced
    ⇒ @sensitive attr = surface-sugar for IFC-labels
    ⇒ PRIME-DIRECTIVE = soundness-theorem of CSSLv3

  R2 : Pony-6-caps ←→ linear × handler interaction (R8)
    ⇒ iso/trn/ref/val/box/tag = deny-aliases matrix
    ⇒ ref = shared-mutable-via-gen-ref (Vale interop)
    ⇒ tag = opaque-handle (no-deref — H<T> subsumes)
    ⇒ iso + handler-one-shot-resume = linear-resource effect-safe

  R3 : Racket-hygiene macros ←→ Futamura-P3 (R9)
    ⇒ hygienic-bindings = syntactic-closure = partial-eval-input
    ⇒ comptime-macro = staged-computation-α-case
    ⇒ ∴ R3 ≡ R9 shared-substrate (macros = hand-written-specializer)

  R4 : bespoke-x86-64 backend ←→ MLIR-core (R6)
    ⇒ MLIR llvm-dialect → drop-to-CLIF-equivalent-custom
    ⇒ stage0 Cranelift-expedient / stage1 own-backend
    ⇒ own-backend ≡ ∀ CSSLv3-IR-node maps to-owned-codegen
    ⇒ no-Rust-compiler-dep in final artifact (self-bootstrap)

  R5 : cross-platform-GPU (Vulkan+D3D12+Metal+GNM+NVN+WebGPU)
    ⇒ SPIR-V = portable-IR-substrate already
    ⇒ per-target lowering = mechanical ¬ design-work
    ⇒ target-profile @ effect-row • {Target<vk|d3d|metal|gnm|nvn|webgpu>}

  R6 : MLIR-from-day-one ←→ R4 + R9
    ⇒ CSSLv3-MIR = MLIR-dialect ⇒ Linalg + Affine + Transform-dialect free
    ⇒ Transform-dialect = F4-staging + macro-expansion hosting-layer
    ⇒ drop to-llvm-dialect-OR-spirv-dialect-OR-own-dialect
    ⇒ own-dialect = CSSLv3-MIR-proper (structured-by-construction)

  R7 : dual-surface (CSLv3-native + Rust-hybrid)
    ⇒ both parse→same-HIR
    ⇒ CSLv3-native = Apocky+Claude-primary
    ⇒ Rust-hybrid = external-contributor / tutorial / docs
    ⇒ formatter round-trips ASCII↔Unicode↔CSLv3-glyph

  R8 : handler × linear-type full-integration
    ⇒ linear-value through-handler = one-shot-resume only
    ⇒ ≡ Eio-lineage (OCaml-5) proven pattern
    ⇒ typesystem-enforced : multi-shot + linear = compile-error
    ⇒ Koka-style evidence-passing + Perceus-RC for non-linear values
    ⇒ Borretti-impossibility dissolved : it-was-traditional-exceptions-specific

  R9 : Futamura-P3 ←→ R3 + F4-staging
    ⇒ P1 : spec(int, src) → compiled-prog (F4 @staged basic)
    ⇒ P2 : spec(spec, int) → compiler
    ⇒ P3 : spec(spec, spec) → compiler-generator
    ⇒ ≡ CSSLv3 bootstraps-self via P3 ↔ R4-own-backend ≡ P3-instance
    ⇒ ≡ domain-DSL compiles via P2 (free compiler-per-DSL)

  R10 : SMT-backed refinement (Z3 / CVC5)
    ⇒ LiquidHaskell-style SMT-discharge
    ⇒ Lipschitz-proof @ compile-time (not bounded-prop approximation)
    ⇒ SDF-convergence-proofs
    ⇒ refinement-solver-plugin = effect-row {Verify<proof-method>}

  R11 : Jets<T,N> higher-order AD
    ⇒ N-th-order Taylor-expansion tracked-in-type
    ⇒ MIR-level : @differentiable fn emits jet-tuple-fn
    ⇒ ∞-order via lazy-jet (co-inductive stream)
    ⇒ differential-geometry usable-directly

  R12 : inverse-rendering/fluids as stdlib-examples
    ⇒ ∀ @differentiable × {GPU} enables-inverse
    ⇒ stdlib demonstrates : shape-from-image, material-estimation,
      initial-condition-recovery for fluids, NN-surrogate-training

  R13 : orthogonal-persistence hot-reload (Pharo-class)
    ⇒ engine-state = image-snapshot (S-expr + gen-ref graph)
    ⇒ compiler-version-change = state migrated via schema-diff
    ⇒ @hot_reload_preserve attribute = persistence-root
    ⇒ feel.toml shim → full-image-swap-and-resume

  R14 : console/mobile/web targets v1
    ⇒ PS5-GNM, Xbox-D3D12X, Switch-NVN, Metal-via-MoltenVK-OR-native,
      WebGPU-via-Tint-WGSL
    ⇒ stub-per-platform-lowering-path, typesystem-untouched
    ⇒ effect {Target<...>} gates platform-specific capabilities

  R15 : vertical-slice = FLOOR not CEILING
    ⇒ add : volumetric-atmosphere, cloud (NUBIS-3), hair/fur-strand,
      water (FFT-ocean + caustics), spectral-path-tracing,
      XeSS2-neural-upscaling-inline, audio-DSP-unified
    ⇒ ≡ "Dreams-level rendering tech + Teardown-destruction
          + PoE2-radiance-cascades + inline-neural-FX
          + spectral-correctness" single-lang single-binary

  R16 : C99 reproducibility anchor from-stage0
    ⇒ ∀ compiler-version emits-C99-tarball (not just stage3)
    ⇒ zig1.wasm-cope avoided
    ⇒ ∀ commit = reproducible-from-published-C-source
    ⇒ PRIME-DIRECTIVE-audit : anyone-can-verify consent=OS code

  R17 : full effect-set extensions
    existing : {NoAlloc, NoRecurse, Deadline<N>, DetRNG, GPU, CPU, XMX, RT,
                SIMD256, Region<'r>, Alloc, Yield, State<S>, Exn<E>, IO,
                Sensitive<dom>}
    add :
      {NoUnbounded}        — ∀ loop/recurse/alloc bounded-comptime
      {Realtime<priority>} — OS-scheduler class
      {Power<budget_mW>}   — thermal/battery budget
      {Thermal<limit_C>}   — die-temp ceiling (R18-backed on Intel)
      {NUMA<node>}         — memory-affinity
      {Cache<level>}       — cache-locality hint
      {Audit<dom>}         — mandatory signed-chain log
      {Reversible}         — undo-able op (replay/time-rewind gameplay)
      {PureDet}            — bit-exact cross-machine reproducible
      {Target<platform>}   — R14 platform-gate
      {Verify<method>}     — R10 SMT-proof required
      {Privilege<level>}   — R1 IFC capability tier
      {Telemetry<scope>}   — R18 instrumentation capture-ring
      {Backend<api>}       — R18 vulkan|levelzero|d3d12|metal|webgpu

  R18 : Level-Zero-as-compute-backend ⊕ telemetry ⊕ test-harness
    ⇒ Intel-direct-to-metal compute-API (not replacement for Vulkan)
    ⇒ SPIR-V input ≡ rspirv-emit unchanged • host-submission divergent
    ⇒ backend-matrix :
        Vulkan-1.4 : graphics + RT + compute ∀ portable
        Level-Zero : compute + XMX + power + sysman ∀ Intel-deep
        D3D12      : Windows-native • R14
        Metal      : Apple • R14
        WebGPU     : browser • R14

    § §§ R18.telemetry  ← lang-level-instrumentation
      effect {Telemetry<scope>} :
        scope ∈ {Off, Wallclock, Counters, FullTrace, GpuFrequency,
                 PowerMW, ThermalC, DispatchLatency, CacheHit, SubgroupOccupancy,
                 MemoryBandwidth, XmxUtilization, RtRaysPerSec}
      Level-Zero zes* calls = effect-discharge-backing
        zesPowerGetEnergyCounter → {PowerMW} + {Telemetry<PowerMW>}
        zesTemperatureGetState → {Thermal<C>} enforcement
        zesFrequencyGetState → {GpuFrequency}
        ze_device_memory_access_properties_t → cache/memory telemetry
      non-Intel fallback : PAPI (Linux perf), ETW (Windows), metal-HUD (Apple)
      compiler-auto-instrument :
        @staged-expansion can-emit telemetry-probes per-usage-site
        probes compiled-out if-{Telemetry<Off>} (zero-overhead)
        probes stream to ring-buffer + optional-OpenTelemetry-exporter
      telemetry-as-first-class-type :
        type TelemetryRing<N : usize> : linear-unique<fixed-size>
        ops : push(sample) read_snapshot() → SnapshotImage
      PRIME-DIRECTIVE-interop :
        {Audit<dom>} + {Telemetry<scope>} compose : signed-counter-chain
        anyone-can-verify runtime-claims from captured-ring

    § §§ R18.test-harness  ← testing-fundamentally-changed
      v1-LoA-testing = unit-tests + frame-capture-diff + spirv-val
      v2-CSSLv3-testing (what-R18-enables) :

        property-based : QuickCheck/Hypothesis-style
          refinement-types generate-well-typed-inputs
          ex : fn foo(x : f32{v : -1 ≤ v ≤ 1}) → generator-derived

        differential-testing : Vulkan vs Level-Zero same-SPIR-V
          ∀ compute-kernel emitted both-backends
          inputs identical-seeded (DetRNG)
          outputs bit-compared ≡ driver-bug-detector
          ≡ found 30-second-turnaround on driver-regressions

        metamorphic-testing : algebraic-laws
          (a + b) + c ≡ a + (b + c) for @PureDet-tagged fns
          rotation-composition laws for mat4-ops
          SDF invariant : |sdf(p) - sdf(p + ε·n)| ≤ k·ε (Lipschitz-check)

        power-regression : {Power<budget_mW>} breach = test-fail
          historical baseline stored ∀ benchmark
          commit increases mean-power >5% ≡ CI-fail
          ≡ thermal-correctness part-of-green-build

        thermal-stress : run-benchmark until-thermal-stable
          zesTemperatureGetState sampled
          assert steady-state below-limit
          ≡ catches inefficient-shader-before-ship

        frequency-stability : zesFrequencyGetState
          assert GPU-not-throttling during hot-path
          ≡ catches driver-issues + OS-scheduling anomalies

        latency-percentile : dispatch-latency histogram
          p99 < budget-or-fail
          Level-Zero command-list enables <1us measurements
          ≡ realtime-audio-callback verification-in-CI

        fuzz-with-oracles : refinement-types + SMT
          fuzzer-input constrained by-refinement-type
          SMT-oracle verifies output-refinement holds
          ≡ replaces ad-hoc fuzz-harnesses

        replay-tests : {Reversible} + {PureDet}
          record session → replay deterministically
          golden-frame-compare ≡ regression-detector
          ≡ Apocky's LoA-playtest-capture as-testsuite

        hot-reload-invariance : R13-orthopersist
          save image → mutate compiler → reload → state-equivalent
          ≡ verifies schema-migration correctness

      testing moves-from : "does-it-work-today"
                 to   : "does-it-meet-power+thermal+latency+
                         determinism+reversibility+consent contracts"
      ≡ CI becomes-a-proof-system ¬ just-smoke-tests

    § §§ R18.integration-map
      → adds 14_BACKEND Level-Zero column
      → adds 04_EFFECTS {Telemetry<scope>} {Backend<api>} {Thermal<C>}
      → adds 17_JETS + 05_AUTODIFF telemetry for grad-norm tracking
      → adds 22_TELEMETRY (new spec) — ring-buffer schema + exporters
      → adds 23_TESTING (new spec) — test-harness + oracle modes
      → PRIME-DIRECTIVE §§ 11_IFC gains-signed-chain-via-telemetry
      → 10_HW gets Intel-dGPU-vs-iGPU sysman-availability table

§ CROSS-CUTTING-INVARIANTS  ← §§ S2.3
  CC1 : consent=OS structurally-enforced (not conventionally)
  CC2 : engine-primitives are-lang-primitives
  CC3 : CPU ≡ GPU ≡ console ≡ mobile ≡ web — effect-row-gated only
  CC4 : structured-by-construction MIR
  CC5 : single-source → all-targets ≡ no-preprocessor-permutation
  CC6 : zero-runtime beyond necessary
  CC7 : reversibility + reproducibility
  CC8 : density=sovereignty (Apocky-core-invariant)
  CC9 : observability ≡ first-class (R18)
    ⇒ ∀ resource-consumption (time power thermal memory) knowable-at-compile
    ⇒ telemetry-probe = compiler-generated ¬ hand-written
    ⇒ "untraced" is itself an effect-annotation ({Telemetry<Off>})
    ⇒ ≡ debugging = reading-the-audit-chain (signed, reproducible)

§ PRIME-DIRECTIVE PROPAGATION  ← §§ S2.4
  layer                    encoding
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  typesystem              IFC-labels (secret<T, principal>)
  effects                 {Sensitive<dom>}, {Audit<dom>}, {Privilege<lvl>}
                          {Telemetry<scope>}, {Power<mW>}, {Thermal<C>}
  attributes              @sensitive, @privileged, @auditable
  stdlib                  refuses harm-oriented effect-compositions
  compiler                rejects-builds violating PRIME-DIRECTIVE soundness
  runtime                 signed-audit-chain via R18-telemetry-ring
  bootstrap               C99-reproducible ≡ third-party-auditable
  tools                   Claude-instance reads-audit-log as-sovereign-peer
  testing                 R18-oracle-modes verify-contracts-continuously
  I> ≡ PRIME-DIRECTIVE = soundness-theorem + signed-runtime-witness

